rComments: A nice person, not a good professor. She's an extremely tough grader, especially for a 2nd year course. Lectures didn't have much structure, she often went off topic. Rarely got responses from emails. I spent hours every day reading the required books. We read a novel a week, some 100 pgs, others 500 pgs.

Lots & lots of reading but totally worth it. The class in general was well-structured but the lectures are freeform and she can go off-topic easily. She has incredibly lenient due dates, but if you get the work in on time she gives good feedback to help you improve. Lots of participation marks too. Favourite course of the semester by far.

She is a nice person, but unfortunately, not a great prof. The class is hardly structured, she does not share her high expectations for assignments, and she is very hard to get a hold of outside of class. Online lectures were brutal to get through. Rarely any guidance. Peers and I have sent numerous emails and have received nothing in return.

Amal is a very informal professor. She is usually late guidance, but due dates are flexible to compensate. Students able to distract her, so classes go off subject often. She really cares. She'll give you good feedback on your poetry. Make sure to put in full effort for full return. I would recommend pairing this course and prof with a busy sem
